</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<bibRefCitation author="Schmidt, O" journalOrPublisher="Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" title="Die Spongien der Kueste von Algier" volumeTitle="Mit Nachtraegen zu den Spongien des Adriatischen Meeres (Drittes Supplement)" year="1868">Schmidt (1868)</bibRefCitation>
gave hardly any description (some vague remarks on the megascleres of 
<taxonomicName class="Demospongiae" family="Pachastrellidae" genus="Pachastrella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pachastrella monilifera" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="monilifera">Pachastrella monilifera</taxonomicName>
grading into a statement on the Red Sea specimen), but the drawings of the microscleres show a sanidaster and a globular aster. Keller claims to have had access to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Schmidt’s">Schmidt's</normalizedToken>
type specimen, but he faithfully reports that there is a discrepancy between 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Schmidt’s">Schmidt's</normalizedToken>
original label and the label of his redescribed specimen, e.g. the original collector was stated to be Ehrenberg by Schmidt, but Keller states it is Siemens, which is probably the correct one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<bibRefCitation author="Maldonado, M" editor="Hooper, JNA" journalOrPublisher="Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publications, New York" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="141 - 162" title="Pachastrellidae" volumeTitle="Systema Porifera. A guide to the classification of sponges" year="2002">
<pageBreakToken pageId="32" pageNumber="33" start="start">Maldonado</pageBreakToken>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
assigned 
<taxonomicName class="Demospongiae" family="Pachastrellidae" genus="Pachastrella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pachastrella exostotica" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="exostotica">Pachastrella exostotica</taxonomicName>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Sollas, 1888" authorityName="Sollas" authorityYear="1888" class="Demospongiae" family="Pachastrellidae" genus="Stoeba" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stoeba" order="Astrophorida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">Stoeba</taxonomicName>
and declared 
<taxonomicName authority="de Laubenfels, 1936" authorityName="de Laubenfels" authorityYear="1936" class="Demospongiae" family="Ancorinidae" genus="Halinastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Halinastra" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">Halinastra</taxonomicName>
a junior synonym of that genus. However, he possibly overlooked that 
<bibRefCitation author="Pulitzer-Finali, G" journalOrPublisher="Annali del Museo civico di storia naturale Giacomo Doria" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="65 - 216" title="A collection of West Indian Demospongiae (Porifera). In appendix, a list of the Demospongiae hitherto recorded from the West Indies." volume="86" year="1986">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pulitzer-Finali’s">Pulitzer-Finali's</normalizedToken>
(1986)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authority="de Laubenfels, 1936" authorityName="de Laubenfels" authorityYear="1936" class="Demospongiae" family="Calthropellidae" genus="Pachataxa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pachataxa lutea" order="Astrophorida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="lutea">Pachataxa lutea</taxonomicName>
possesses similar spiculation as 
<taxonomicName authority="de Laubenfels, 1936" authorityName="de Laubenfels" authorityYear="1936" class="Demospongiae" family="Calthropellidae" genus="Pachataxa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pachataxa exostotica" order="Astrophorida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="exostotica">Pachataxa exostotica</taxonomicName>
(see below). With at least two species sharing the peculiar aster-like compressed acanthorhabds, (and several further species with diversified aster shapes, see below) there is good reason to maintain 
<taxonomicName authority="de Laubenfels, 1936" authorityName="de Laubenfels" authorityYear="1936" class="Demospongiae" family="Ancorinidae" genus="Halinastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Halinastra" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">Halinastra</taxonomicName>
as a distinct taxon, proposed here to be a subgenus.
</paragraph>
